`Please give a upvote if you like else comment for any doubts.`

**Approach:** The idea is to use traverse the tree recursively and in each recursive calls return a pair of minimum element, maximum element and the current subtree is BST or not. After each Left and Right recursive calls ends check if the root having these LST and RST follows the BST property or not. If found to be true then return the corresponding pairs to it's parent.

Below is the implementation of the same:

```
class Solution {
public:

    // From each recursive calls return the
    // minimum, maximum and isBST flag for
    // each subtree
    pair<pair<long long int, long long int>, bool> dfs(TreeNode *root) {

        // If root is NULL then it is BST
        // return the MAX, MIN, true
        // and MAX is return as minimum value 
        // to validate the BST property for node
        // having at least 1 leaf node`
        if(root == NULL) {
            return {{LLONG_MAX, LLONG_MIN}, true};
        }

        // Left and Right Calls
        pair<pair<long long int, long long int>, bool> P1 = dfs(root->left);
        pair<pair<long long int, long long int>, bool> P2 = dfs(root->right);

        // Find the if the current root is BST
        // LST and RST is also BST
        bool ans = P1.second && P2.second
                    && (root->val > P1.first.second
                        && root->val < P2.first.first);

        // Find the current minimum in the subtree
        // rooted at current root with minimum of
        // LST and RST and current root->value
        long long int minimum = min(1LL*root->val,
                                    min(P1.first.first,
                                        P2.first.first));

        // Find the current maximum in the subtree
        // rooted at current root with minimum of
        // LST and RST and current root->value
        long long int maximum = max(1LL*root->val,
                                    max(P1.first.second,
                                        P2.first.second));

        // Return the corresponding pair for
        // each recursive calls
        return {{minimum, maximum}, ans};
    }

    bool isValidBST(TreeNode* root) {

        if(root->left == NULL
           and root->right == NULL) return true;

        pair<pair<long long int, long long int>, bool> P = dfs(root);
        return P.second;
    }
};
```
*Time Complexity: O(N)
Auxiliary Space: O(H), where H is the maximum height of the tree.*

