# Intuition
- We start by assuming that we have robbed the first house. (prev = nums[0])
- Hence we can't pick the just next element. 
- If we robb the house which is 2nd to the the current index ( if(i>1) non-adjacent). We have to add that money. 
- And if we do not pick the house to robb. We are left with 1st house money. 
- Lastly we take the max of both the conditions. And update the variables for further computations. 

# Approach
- We start using pick and Not pick method. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N) Single Pass 
- Space complexity: O(1) No extra Space 

