# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Simple Memoization, inspired by 0/1 knapsack.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Take element at index i or skip it.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(2^n)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n)

# Code
```
import java.lang.*;
class Solution {

    public int helper(int[] nums, int i,HashMap<Integer,Integer> memo){
        if(memo.containsKey(i)){
            return memo.get(i);
        }
        if(i >= nums.length){
            return 0;
        }
        int notTake = 0;
        int take= nums[i]+helper(nums,i+2,memo);
        if (i < nums.length-1)    
            notTake = nums[i+1]+helper(nums,i+3,memo);
        memo.put(i,Math.max(take,notTake));
        return memo.get(i);
    }
    public int rob(int[] nums) {
        return helper(nums,0, new HashMap<Integer,Integer>());
    }
}
```

