solutions.content:
**Approach 01 : Memoization/Top-Down DP (aka Recursive DP)**

Idea : In every state of DP we have only two choice , eighter we will include current element in our result (with under the condition)  or we will skip the current (for be more banifited)

**Code :**
```
class Solution {
public:

    int solve(int now , vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& DP){
        if(now >= nums.size()){
            return 0;
        }
        int &ret = DP[now];
        if(ret != -1) return ret;

        int w1 = 0, w2 = 0;
        w1 = solve(now+1, nums, DP);
        w2 = nums[now] + solve(now+2, nums, DP); 
        return ret = max(w1, w2);;
    }

    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {
        int N = nums.size();
        vector<int>DP(N, -1);

        int result = solve(0, nums, DP);
        return result;
    }
};
```

Time Complexity : **O(N)**
Space Complexity : **O(N)** for iterate all of the N item + **O(N)** space also required for Recursion stack Memory
so Total Space will be : **O(N)+O(N) ~ O(N)**.


**Approach 02 : Tabulation/ Buttom-Up DP (aka Iterative DP)**

Idea : Idea is as simple as approach 01.

**Code : **

```
class Solution {
public:
    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {
        int N = nums.size();

        if(N==0) return 0;
        if(N==1) return nums[0];

        vector<int>DP(N);
        DP[0] = nums[0];
        DP[1] = max(nums[0], nums[1]);

        for(int i=2; i<N; i++){
            DP[i] = max(DP[i-1], nums[i]+ DP[i-2]);
        }
        return DP[N-1];
    }
};
```

Time Complexity : **O(N)** 
Space Complexity : **O(N)** , we omitted our recursion stack memory here :)

**Approach 03: Space Optimization of Approach 02.**

Idea : In approach 02 , we clearly see that we need only last two value for compute the current state. so we don't need to store all previous state's value at all. Here we will store only **previous** and **secondPrevious** value for compute the **current state**.

**Code : **

```
class Solution {
public:
    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {
        int N = nums.size();
        if(N==1) return nums[0];

        int prev = nums[0], secondPrev = 0, current;

        for(int i=1; i<N; i++){

            current = nums[i] + secondPrev;
            current = max(current, prev);

            secondPrev = prev;
            prev = current;
        }
        return prev;
    }
};
```

Time Complexity : **O(N)** , to comute every state of DP.
Space Complexity : **O(1)**, we use only constant space here.


