Scenario with 1 house and 2 houses can be decided. For 3 houses scenario, your choices are 
what you would choose with 1 house plus current house OR what you would choose with 2 houses.
Likewise, with 4 houses, your choices are what you would choose in 2 houses scenario plus the current house OR just what you would choose with 3 houses.
Therefor with N houses, your choices are f(n - 2) + Nth house OR f(n-1).
```
class Solution {
    public int rob(int[] nums) {
        if (nums.length == 1)
            return nums[0];
        if (nums.length == 2)
            return Math.max(nums[0], nums[1]);

        int maxSum = 0;
        int scheme1 = nums[0];
        int scheme2 = Math.max(nums[0], nums[1]);

        for (int i = 2; i < nums.length; i++){
            maxSum = Math.max(scheme1 + nums[i], scheme2);
            scheme1 = scheme2;
            scheme2 = maxSum;
        }

        return maxSum;
    }
}
```

