The robber can rob only choose the maximum of previous maximum nums but not adjacent ones. So take the max of i-2 and i-3.

```
class Solution:
	def rob(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
		if len(nums) <= 2:
			return max(nums)
		nums[2] = nums[0] + nums[2]
		for i in range(3, len(nums)):
			nums[i] = nums[i] + max(nums[i-2], nums[i-3])
		return max(nums)
```

