Note: the probem says you can not rob alternate house and we need to rob maximum value, so we can observe  that we if we choose to rob house[i] then we cann't rob house[i+1], we have to rob from house[i+2].
hence you got two choices and we'll take maximum of them
  1. To rob ith-house and jump to (i+2)th-house
       amount_when_ith_house_choosen=amount[i] + amount from (i+2)th to last house
  2. To not rob i-th house and move to (i+1)th house
    	amount_when_ith_house_not_choosen=amount from (i+1)th to last house   
So, we will continue searching till we reach the end and store the maximum amount robbed from both the choices into an array
The last index of the array will be the aanswer.

dp[i] = max( dp[i-2] + amount[i] , dp[i-1]) = max(choose to rob i-th house, choose not to rob i-th house)


