solutions.content:
Define `fn(i)` as the maximum amount of money after robbing `i`th house. Then, below recursive relation holds 

`fn(i) = max(fn(i-1), fn(i-2) + nums[i])` for `i >= 0` and `fn(i) = 0` for `i < 0`;

As a result, it can be solved using dynamic programming. 

top-down implementation (`O(N)` time & `O(N)` space)
```
class Solution:
    def rob(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:

        @lru_cache(None)
        def fn(i):
            """Return the maximum amount of money robbing up to ith house."""
            if i < 0: return 0
            return max(fn(i-1), fn(i-2) + nums[i])

        return fn(len(nums)-1)
```

bottom-up implementation (`O(N)` time & `O(1)` space)
```
class Solution:
    def rob(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
        f0 = f1 = 0
        for x in nums: f0, f1 = f1, max(f1, f0+x)
        return f1
```

