For recursion + memoization,
What do you memoize? surely we aren't memoizing a list of ints?
```
@cache
def recur(nums):
  ...
  first = nums[0]
  rest = nums[1:]
  r_rest = nums[2:]
  return max(add(first, recur(r_rest)),
                      recur(rest))
return recur(nums)
```

Why is the statement `memo[i] = max(dp(i-2) + nums[i], dp(i-1))` faster(95% of python submission) than statement `memo[i] = dp(i-1)) + max(dp(i-2) + nums[i]` (45%) in top down approach?

```
