OPTIMAL SOLUTION (C++)
Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Logic: 
We have two options, either to rob a house or leave it.

CASE 1 (rob a house):
We can  rob a house if we haven't robbed the previous one. So maximum rob amount till that house will be maximum robbed money till i-2th house + ith house.

CASE 2 (not rob a house):
In this case maximum robbed amount will be maximum robbed till i-1th house as we are not robbing the ith one.

And finally maximum of these two cases will be the final maximum robbed amount for ith house.
Here we need only maximum data for i-1th and i-2th house. So we need not keep the data for all the houses, by this we can reduce space complexity from O(N) -> O(1).

class Solution {
public:
    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {
        vector<int> dp(3);
        int n = nums.size();
        dp[0] = 0;
        dp[1] = nums[0];
        if(n==1){
            return dp[1];
        }
        dp[2] = max(nums[0], nums[1]);
        for(int i=3;i<=n;i++){
            dp[0] = dp[1];
            dp[1] = dp[2];
            dp[2] = max(dp[1], dp[0]+nums[i-1]);
        }
        return dp[2];
    }
};

