// Reservoir sample 
// No matter how many targets are in the nums, we can randomly pick one just by one loop.
// Example: {1,2,3,3,3}
// index 2 targets = 1 random pick between [0, 1), so it would be always 0 and pick = 2; Probability is 1
// index 3 targets = 2 random pick between [0, 2), so the probability that index 2 is stay as answer is 1/2 (0 - change index, 1 - not change)
// index 4 targets = 3 random pick between [0, 3), so the probability that index 2 is stay as answer is 2/3 (0 - change index, 1-2 - not change)
// To sum up index 2 probability is = 1 * 1/2 * 2/3 = 1/3
// 
// Probability for index 3 will be 1/2 * 2/3 = 1/3 
// Probability for index 4 will be 1/3 = 1/3****

