for evry dup, keep looping random.nextInt(++cnt), the possibility to stay in result would be 1/cnt;
for example, 
1, if we have only one at idex 0, value 2, so far, prob is 1/1;
2, now, we get idx 3, value 2, reservoir2, prob of idx 0 remains equal to idx 3 not randomized, 1/1 * (1- 1/2) = 1/2;
3,similar,  we get idx 7, value 2, reservoir 3, prob of idx 0 remains, 1/1 * (1 -1/2) * (1 - 1/3) = 1/3;
...
n,  reservoir n, 1 * 1/2 * 2/3 * ... (n-1)/n = 1/n;

similarly for all other idx, the prob is also 1/n;
That is why it is "equal opportunity", sounds like a good political word.


