solutions.content:
The [top voted solution](https://leetcode.com/problems/random-pick-index/discuss/88072/Simple-Reservoir-Sampling-solution) is amazing which is based on reservoir sampling. While when you look up this algorithm, it looks different which may confuse you.

So, I want to show you how we can use the standard reservoir sampling template for this question. It may help you to understand the top voted solution. For the algorithm itself, you can checkout the [wiki](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reservoir_sampling#Simple_algorithm).

1. Standard template:
```
public int[] sampling(int[] dataStream, int k) {
  int[] reservoir = new int[k];
  // fill the reservoir
  for (int i = 0; i < reservoir.length; i++) {
      reservoir[i] = dataStream[i];
  }
 // replace element in reservoir when condition met
  for (int i = k; i < dataStream.length; i++) {
      int d = rand.nextInt(i + 1);
      if (d < k) {
        reservoir[d] = dataStream[i];
    }
  }
  return reservoir;
}
```

2. How can we apply the template to this question?
In this question, we only return index for the target value. So, you can image you are only checking the targes - you will fill the reservoir only with target values. 
The question asks to return any ONE index of the target with same possibility. That's the reservoir with size 1. 
So, below is the solution applied to the template.
```
class Solution {
    private int[] dataStream;

    public Solution(int[] dataStream) {
        this.dataStream = dataStream;
    }

    public int pick(int target) {
        Random random = new Random();
        int[] reservoir = new int[1];
        int i = 0;
        int countTargets = 0; // since dataStream has non-target values, we use counter to count how many targets been "processed".

		// fill the reservoir
        for(;i < dataStream.length; ++i) {
            if(dataStream[i] == target) { // only care about target
                reservoir[0] = i;
                ++countTargets;
                break;
            }
        }

		// replace element in reservoir when condition met
        ++i; // next index the stream data can select from
        for(; i < dataStream.length; ++i) {
            if(dataStream[i] != target) { // only care about target
                continue;
            }
            ++countTargets;
            int replaceIndex = random.nextInt(countTargets);
            if(replaceIndex < reservoir.length) {
                reservoir[replaceIndex] = i;
            }
        }
        return reservoir[0];
    }
}
```

