solutions.content:
**Approach:**
1) We will make a static HashMap hm of (Integer mapped to ArrayList<Integer>).
2) When Solution Function is called, we initialise our HashMap hm.
3) Inside the Solution only, we traverse the nums Array and fill the Hashmap.
4) In the HashMap, we map the Value in the nums Array with an ArrayList and this ArrayList contains all the indexes of Value inside the nums Array.
5) When the "Pick" function is called, we first get from the HashMap, the ArrayList mapped to the given target.
6) We find the size of this ArrayList and then using Math.random() function we call the random index from the ArrayList.

```
class Solution {
    HashMap<Integer,ArrayList<Integer>> hm;

    public Solution(int[] nums) {
        hm=new HashMap<>(); //Initialising the HashMap

        //Traverse the nums array and fill the HashMap
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++)
        {
            ArrayList<Integer> idxArr=hm.getOrDefault(nums[i],new ArrayList<Integer>());
            idxArr.add(i);
            hm.put(nums[i],idxArr);
        }
    }

    public int pick(int target) {
        ArrayList<Integer> idxArr=hm.get(target); //Get the ArrayList mapped to the given "target" value

        int size=idxArr.size(); //Find the size of this ArrayList

		//Using Math.random() find the randomIdx in the range 0 to size-1
        int randomIdx=(int)(Math.random()*size); 

        return idxArr.get(randomIdx); //Return the value from the ArrayList at the randomIdx
    }
}
```

