solutions.content:
**Approach 1: Reservoir Sampling**

Reservior Sampling allows us randomly choose ```k``` samples from ```n``` items, where n is either too large or even unknown. 

For this particular question, ```k = 1```. We need to make the probability of choosing each ```target``` is ```1/count``` where count is the number of ocurrence of ```target```.
- When the 1st ```target``` occurs, we have no choices but to choose it, so ```P(target1) = 1```.
- When the 2nd ```target``` occurs, we choose it with ```1/2``` probability, so ```P(target2) = 1/2```. 
	- At this time, ```P(target1) = 1 * 1/2 = 1/2```.
		- ```1```: probability of being chosen from the previous round.
		- ```1/2```:  probability of not being replaced in current round.
- When the 3rd ```target``` occurs, we choose it with ```1/3``` probability, so```P(target3) = 1/3```.
	- At this time,  ```P(target1) = P(target2) = 1/2* (1-1/3)= 1/3```.
		- ```1/2```: probability of being chosen from the previous round.
		- ```1-1/3```:  probability of not being replaced in current round.
-  ...
-  For the i-th target, ```P(target i) = 1/i * [1- 1/(i+1)]* [1 - 1/(i+2)] * ...* (1 - 1/n) = 1/n = 1/n ```.
		-  ```1/i ```: probability of being chosen in ```i-th``` round.
		-  ```[1- 1/(i+1)]```: probability of not being replaced in ```(i+1)-th``` round.
		-  ```[1- 1/(i+2)]```: probability of not being replaced in ```(i+2)-th``` round.
		-  ...
		-  ```[1 - 1/n]```: probability of not being replaced in ```n-th``` round.

**Complexity**
- Time: O(n)
- Space: O(1)

```
public class Solution {

    private int[] arr;
    private Random random;

    public Solution(int[] nums) {

        random = new Random();

        arr = new int[nums.Length];
        for(int i = 0; i < arr.Length; i++)
            arr[i] = nums[i];
    }

    public int Pick(int target) {

        int res = -1, cnt = 0; 
        for(int i = 0; i < arr.Length; i++)
        {
            if(arr[i] == target)
            {
                cnt++;

                // Reservoir Sampling
                // Choose i-th target with probability of 1/cnt
                // random.Next(0,cnt) return an random value between 0 and cnt-1 inclusively
                // so the probability that random value is 0 is 1/cnt
                int randomIdx = random.Next(0,cnt);
                if(randomIdx == 0)
                    res = i;
            }
        }

        return res;
    }
}
