# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N*N) We are traversing each element once!

- Space complexity:
  O(1) As no additional DS is used appart from the required one

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[] findDiagonalOrder(int[][] mat) {

        int row = 0;
        int col = 0;
        int m = mat.length;
        int n = mat[0].length;
        int res [] = new int [m * n];

        for(int i=0; i<res.length; i++) {
            res[i] = mat[row][col];

            if((row + col) % 2 == 0) {
                // Forward diagnol
                if(col == n-1) {
                    // We cannot go right , have to go down now
                    row ++;
                } else if(row == 0) {
                    // We cannot go up, have to go right
                    col ++;
                } else {
                    row --;
                    col ++;
                }
            } else {
                // Backward diagnol
                if(row == m-1) {
                    // We cannot go down , have to go right
                    col ++;
                } else if(col == 0) {
                    // We cannot go left , have to go down now
                    row ++; 
                } else {
                    row ++;
                    col --;
                }
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

