# Intuition
I'm surprised how many people find this task difficult...

# Approach
We know that at each operation `[a, b]` all values in range `[0..a][0..b]` will be incremented. Hence our task is to find a range which will be incremented by all operations. To do that we simply find the **minimum row and column indexes** of all operations. 
Think about it a little: this range is the **maximum intersection** of ranges of all operations. Thus number of elements is `min_row_index * min_column_index`.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int maxCount(int m, int n, int[][] ops) {
        for (var op: ops) {
            if (op[0] < m) m = op[0];
            if (op[1] < n) n = op[1];
        }
        return m * n;
    }
}
```

