solutions.content:
Your answer is going to be the area with the most overlapping ranges in the collection. Since all overlapping ranges begin in the same corner of the matrix, another way to think about it is the answer will be the product of the smallest m and n values in the collection since the area created by those values will overlap the most with every other area. So, you can just iterate through the pairs to find the smallest m and n values given and return their product.

```
class Solution {
    public int maxCount(int m, int n, int[][] ops) {
        for(int[] vals : ops) {
            m = vals[0] < m ? vals[0] : m;
            n = vals[1] < n ? vals[1] : n;
        }
        return m * n;
    }
}
```

