# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
after reading the question it is clearly observed  that the product of the smallest operation in ops[m][n] (where n<2;m=length of ops array) array will give the number of elments with the highest  value.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
after more refining the thought and taking some demo example i came to a conclusion that the number of elements have hightest value will be the product of the smallest number  from the first and second  column. so make a loop to trverse through array (ops) and extract the smallest from each column by using min max function.  

