# Approach
The window having the most incremented value will be the smallest overlapping window, hence find the smallest window and output the number of elements in that window by getting the product of row and column.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n), as the there is a single iteration through the ops.
# Code
```
import java.util.*;
class Solution {
    public int maxCount(int m, int n, int[][] ops) {
        /*
        find the smallest window [a, b] in ops
        find the n of elem in the window
        */
        int[] smallestOp = new int[]{m, n};
        for (int[] op: ops){
            smallestOp[0] = Math.min(op[0], smallestOp[0]);
            smallestOp[1] = Math.min(op[1], smallestOp[1]);
        }

        return smallestOp[0] * smallestOp[1];
    }
}
```

