# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Basically we have to find the size of the rectangle that was included in most operations.
The main idea is that that we will always have a rectangle in the left upper corner. 
**Why?** 
Because we always increase the elements of the matrix from 0 to ops\[i][0] and from 0 to ops\[i][1].
Thus we have to find the smallest rectangle that ever appeared. That means that we just have to find the minimum row and column that are in our operations matrix.

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int maxCount(int m, int n, int[][] ops) {
        if (ops.length == 0) return m * n;

        int row = ops[0][0], col = ops[0][1];

        for(int i = 0; i < ops.length; ++i) {
            if (row > ops[i][0]) row = ops[i][0];
            if (col > ops[i][1]) col = ops[i][1];
        }

        return row * col;
    }
}
```

