# Intuition

We don't need to count incrementions, all we need is to find most common intersection for all operations

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$, where n - the number of operations

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int maxCount(int m, int n, int[][] ops) {
        if (ops == null || ops.length == 0) {
            return m * n;
        }

        int x = m;
        int y = n;

        for (int[] op : ops) {
            int opx = op[0];
            int opy = op[1];

            if (opx < x) {
                x = opx;
            }

            if (opy < y) {
                y = opy;
            }
        }

        return x * y;
    }
}
```

